[[Image:aerialimagecamera.jpg|thumb|150px|A special effects movie camera stand with aerial image capabilities.]]
An '''aerial image''' is a projected image which is "floating in air", and cannot be viewed normally. It can only be seen from one position in space, often focused by another lens. 

Aerial image technology was used in [[optical printer]]s and movie [[special effects]] photography before the advent of [[computer graphics]] in movie production, and also for combining [[traditional animation|animation]] and live action footage onto one piece of film.

